                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-231-victim2218 t18200918-231-viclabel1332"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18200918-231-crimeloc1333">Vere-street, Clare-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-231-crimeloc1333" type="placeName" value="Vere-street, Clare-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-231-crimeloc1333" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-231-off1330 t18200918-231-crimeloc1333"></join>. On the 23d of August I was at tea in my back-room, and heard a noise at the window, which had been broken, and a plate put against it. I perceived the plate had been knocked down, and a quantity of thimbles gone. Next morning a little boy came to sell me a thimble which I knew to be one of them. He said he lived at No. 9, Steward's-rents, I sent him home. A girl came in and said, a boy was there with a quantity of thimbles. I went there, and found the prisoner laying on the floor on a blanket, and charged him with it. He produced the thimbles and snuff-box.</p>
